data: In the Velvet Room, Igor explains that Personas are strengthened by the bonds one makes with others, and Margaret notes that their guest has formed the bond necessary for the Magician Arcana so far. Chie grows concerned after seeing Yukiko on the Midnight Channel, but is assuaged when Yukiko calls her to say she is taking time off from school to help her family's inn; Yukiko's mother fell ill from stress caused by the investigation of Yamano as she attended the inn prior to her death. Before leaving school, Yu is approached by another student who asks him to join the basketball club, but Yu turns down the offer and heads to Junes with Yosuke and Chie. After confirming with Teddie that no humans are currently inside the TV world, Yu suggests that they watch tonight's Midnight Channel. That night while watching the Midnight Channel, Yu sees Yukiko dressed as a princess proclaiming she is searching for her "Prince Charming" before running off into a castle. The next day, Yosuke reveals two fake swords he found believing they will help in the TV world, but both he and Yu are arrested when an officer notices them. At the station, Dojima and Adachi release the boys as Chie catches up. She reveals that Yukiko has gone missing, prompting Adachi to say that the police believe Yukiko may be involved with the murders. Upset by the accusations, Chie tells the boys that they must go into the TV world to save Yukiko. While exploring Yukiko's Castle, Chie runs in ahead. She enters a room resembling a bedroom where she hears Yukiko's thoughts about being useless without Chie. During this, Chie's other self appears, scoffing at Yukiko and liking how Yukiko submits. When Chie rejects these accusations, her other self transforms into a Shadow that the boys fight, with Yu discovering his ability to use other Persona in battle. After the battle, Chie accepts that the only thing she cares about is Yukiko's friendship, causing the Shadow to transform into her Persona: Tomoe Gozen. The group leave the TV world, unable to find Yukiko, but vowing to rescue her before the fog returns.

Several weeks later, Kanji joins up with the Investigation Team to find out who pushed him and the others into the TV world. That night, Ryotaro asks Yu if he has been getting involved in anything, knowing that he was at Tatsumi Textiles and is worried that Yu is getting in over his head.

The Investigation Team goes to save Rise from the TV world, finding her at the "Marukyu Striptease". However, this causes Teddie to have an existential crisis, bringing forth his Other Self which also turns into a Shadow, sucking Teddie's deflated body up and threatening to kill the others. As Teddie proclaims to his other self that he does not want the easy answers as to who he really is, Rise uses Himiko to detect Teddie's Shadow's weak spot, allowing Izanagi to defeat it, freeing Teddie who accepts his other self and receives his own Persona: Kintoki-Douji.

In the Velvet Room, Margaret tells their guest that he has acquired the bond of the Star Arcana, before Igor warns him that his journey is reaching a climax with surprises in store. Margaret adds that his path is at a crossroads, and if he makes the wrong decisions his journey will come to an end. She reminds him that there is only one truth, before Igor warns him that defeat is not the only way to lose. The Investigation Team enters the TV world to find Mitsuo Kubo in the video game-like Void Quest area. While Teddie deals with Shadows with his Persona, the gang discusses how they believe Kubo is the culprit behind the murders and how Rise, Kanji, and Yukiko have all come into contact with him before they were thrown into the TV world. By the time they track down Mitsuo Kubo, they see him arguing with his other self over the murders, while his other self claims that he is "empty". Once Kubo refuses his other self's statements, it begins to transform into its Shadow form. Suddenly, time skips forward to after the battle, when the Investigation Team is planning a party to celebrate the resolution of the murder case. As time progresses forward through the months, the group starts falling apart, culminating on a rainy day late in November when Yu asks Yosuke if he would like to go to see Teddie, but Yosuke declines. That night, Yu tries to watch the Midnight Channel, but nothing comes on and he cannot even put his hand into the TV. He hears a voice, and discovers that Mitsuo's Shadow is in his room. He attempts to summon a Persona to fight with, but nothing works, as Mitsuo's Shadow taunts him that his bonds are now "empty". He starts to give up hope when the Shadow strangles him until he hears Yosuke's voice and he is pulled out of the illusion the Shadow created. Reunited with his friends, Yu makes a confident retortion to the Shadow that he is "far from empty" and summons several Personas representing all of the bonds he has made in the few months he has spent in Inaba to attack the Shadow, including the new Personas Makami, King Frost, High Pixie, and Leanan Sidhe. When the Shadow is defeated, they confront Mitsuo, who shamelessly admits to being behind the three murders, and they are surprised when his other self disappears instead of turning into a Persona. As in the illusion, Yu proposes that the gang have a celebratory party for Kubo's arrest. After the party, Nanako and Teddie make a promise that he will come over to play with her, and Yosuke tells Yu about the shopping district's summer festival.

In the Velvet Room, Margaret warns their guest that he is becoming lax and that may spell trouble, but Igor says he should move at his own pace, even though danger approaches. Yu sees Naoto Shirogane come on a news program tell the television presenter that there are incongruities in the murder case and that it is still under investigation. The next day after school, the Investigation Team discusses the program when Naoto approaches them to ask them more about their involvement in the murder case. Naoto tells them that they are not seen as possible suspects, but as pawns in the game. Naoto goes on to reveal that Morooka's murder is the only one that sticks out, because he never appeared on TV, did not disappear before his body was discovered, and was the only victim with a cause of death (blunt force to his head). Naoto also states that Mitsuo Kubo's arrest was just a ploy by the police to close the case to ease everyone. Naoto leaves, but repeats what Yukiko said on the trip before, claiming that this case "is not [a] game to [him]". When Naoto's silhouette is seen on the Midnight Channel on the next rainy night, the Investigation Team realizes Naoto must have been right. That night, Naoto's other self comes on the Midnight Channel to say that Naoto will be undergoing an experimental operation to be born anew. The gang goes into the TV world to see if they can find Naoto, but without any substantial information, Rise is unable to pinpoint his location. Yu and Kanji are distracted in their search for information when Kanji is told his mother has gone to the hospital, but she is revealed to be fine and only escorted someone there. While apologizing to Yu at the Chinese Diner Aiya, Kanji asks Aika if she knows anything about Naoto. To Kanji's surprise, they discover that Naoto argued with Adachi over the handling of the case, giving Rise the right information Himiko needs to track Naoto down to the Secret Laboratory. When they enter, Naoto is shown on several television screens chiding her Other Self for acting too much like a child. While the Investigation Team fights several Shadows, Yu summoning Genbu to do so, the other Naoto reveals Naoto's insecurities about being seen only as a child, and despite Naoto's wishes to be seen as a useful manly detective, like the ones in crime and mystery novels, Naoto will never become a man like them because "he" is not really a man at all. The doppelganger's continued egging causes Naoto to reject her other self, transforming it into a Shadow. Shadow Naoto attacks the group with its strange powers, rapidly aging Yosuke, before turning its attack on the others. The Investigation Team retreats as Naoto is left in her Shadow's clutches.

In the Velvet Room, Margaret congratulates their guest for obtaining the Fortune Arcana. She then states that only another heart can bond with another heart, before proposing a toast between herself and Yu Narukami. A hit-and-run occurs at the Samegawa flood plains, with a woman severely hurt. At the Dojima househould, Dojima has made coffee for the family, something he has not done since the death of his wife. He gets an urgent call from Adachi regarding the accident and promptly leaves, which saddens Nanako who wanted him to read her a bedtime story. In the patrol car, Adachi comments on the case's similarity with the death of Dojima's wife. The next day, Yu comes across a photo of Dojima, Nanako, and her mother. Nanako explains that Dojima hid all the photos of her mother after she passed away and wonders if she can keep it; Yu promises to ask Dojima for permission. Later, they go to Junes so Yu can study for his midterms with his friends while Nanako goes on a "date" with Teddie. That night, Yu asks Dojima about the photo but is told to do what he thinks is best. Nanako comes in to give her father a form she got from school but ends up having a stomach ache. Dojima rushes to help her but gets a call from Adachi about a sealed letter for him from a Mr. Ichihara, and immediately heads out, leaving Yu to care for Nanako. A while later, she explains that the form is for parents to sit in on a class but admits that her father likely will not go because of work. The next day, Yu goes to the police station to give Dojima the form and the two end up at the Aiya diner where Dojima explains Mr. Ichihara was his superior and has given him information about the recent hit-and-run. He also reveals that his wife, Chisato, died in a similar accident while on the way to pick Nanako up from preschool. Yu suggests he should pay more attention to Nanako but Dojima snaps at him to mind his own business. That night, Yu gives Nanako the photo of herself and her parents in a frame. She asks him what happens to people after they die, and after he tells her they go to Heaven, she hopes that she will one day see her mother there. The next day, Yu asks Naoto if she can find out anything about Chisato's death, but she says there is not much evidence in the case and claims it will be difficult for the crime to ever be solved. When Dojima comes home, Nanako asks him about the form but he responds that he will probably have to work on the suggested days and therefore cannot attend. She gets upset and runs to her room, prompting Yu to tell Dojima he should spend more time with his daughter instead of constantly trying to solve the hit-and-run. Nanako overhears and asks about it, but Dojima dismisses her question which upsets her even more and prompts her to run out of the house. Yu and Dojima go out looking for her with no luck until Yu remembers his conversation with her about her mother being in Heaven, which allows Dojima to realize that she must be at the Samegawa flood plains. When they find her, Yu has Dojima talk to her and Nanako admits that she thinks he hates her and her mother. Dojima apologizes and promises he will spend more time with her. The next day, they celebrate the three of them becoming a family, and Dojima says he will go to her class observation.

In the Velvet Room, Igor reads their guest's fortune, and Margaret discovers exactly what fate lies in store for their guest. The Investigation Team enters the TV world to find a beautiful realm that looks like Heaven, which Yosuke realizes must be what Nanako really wanted to go to. They hear her voice and find her being dragged along by Namatame, who still says he wants to save her, just like he saved all of the others. They think he wanted them all to face their true selves, but why he did it in such a deadly manner is beyond them. Before they can confront him, he once again proclaims he is the savior when his presence summons many Shadows that possess him and creates Kunino-sagiri, attacking the group, if not for Yu summoning Saturnus to block the attacks. Yu rushes at Kunino-sagiri when it raises its hand, possessing Yu with an antenna over his head, forcing him to attack his friends with Saturnus. The group summons their Personas, and Kanji rushes at Yu with Take-Mikazuchi, with Yu switching to Arahabaki to block the attacks, and then switching to Atropos to attack everyone, once more. Yosuke and Jiraiya rush at him, until Yu switches to Tam Lin to attack Jiraiya, severely hurting Yosuke. The possessed Yu prepares to switch to Beelzebub, much to everyone's shock. Yu tries to stop himself from attacking, while Kunino-sagiri says no one will get in his way. Nanako's voice gets through to Yu, who manages to stop himself, giving the others the chance to attack Beelzebub and Kunino-sagiri. Yu manages to destroy the antenna controlling him to catch Nanako after Kunino-sagiri drops her. However, Kunino-sagiri takes control of the others. Still in pain after grabbing the antenna, Yu hears Dojima's voice asking him to save Nanako, giving him the strength to fuse four Personas into the powerful Kohryu, using the Persona to free his friends, who all use their Personas to attack Kunino-sagiri, destroying him. However, the Shadows that created Kunino-sagiri threaten everyone until Nanako helps Yu summon Sraosha to purify the area of Shadows. Everyone returns to the real world to bring Nanako to the hospital, where she is placed in intensive care. Naoto feels bad that because she questioned Namatame, it took up time to save Nanako, but Yu says she did help out in the end. A couple of weeks later, Inaba is filled with a thick fog, and as Yu, Chie, Yukiko, and Yosuke are on the way to school, Yosuke tells the others that the police are interrogating Namatame, who has awakened. Yu also tells them that Nanako is feeling better, so they can all see her. Rise and Kanji also hear the good news, but Rise could not find Naoto. Yu finds her and tells her about the events, and she realizes that she actually did help out, even if she felt that she could only help out as a detective. The group goes to see Nanako after school, but she is still a little weak. Later, Adachi tells the group that they found info in Namatame's diary that he tried to hit on Saki Konishi which may have led to her death, which angers Yosuke, causing Adachi to leave to check up on Dojima. Yu tells Yosuke not to be upset and he should air his feelings, but he is not ready. As they head home, they pass by people talking about the fog which is very thick lately, reminding them of the fog in the TV world. Just then, Kanji puts on his glasses and urges the others to do so. When they do, they see that the glasses are allowing them to see through the fog, causing Chie to wonder aloud if the fog from the TV world is coming into the real world. A week later, they still cannot figure out why the TV world fog is leaking into their world, until Teddie mentions that now that they have discovered the real killer he has to go back, but he does not want to until Nanako is better. Yu tells him he can stay until then, making him happy. When Chie mentions how cold it has gotten, it reminds Yu that he promised to buy a new kotatsu for Nanako. They all plan to throw a party for Nanako for Christmas when suddenly Yu receives a call from Adachi that Nanako's condition has taken a turn for the worse. He heads to the hospital and sees Nanako just as she appears to die in front of him.

Yu rushes at Kunino-sagiri when it raises its hand, possessing Yu with an antenna over his head, forcing him to attack his friends with Saturnus. The group summons their Personas, and Kanji rushes at Yu with Take-Mikazuchi, with Yu switching to Arahabaki to block the attacks, and then switching to Atropos to attack everyone, once more. Yosuke and Jiraiya rush at him, until Yu switches to Tam Lin to attack Jiraiya, severely hurting Yosuke. The possessed Yu prepares to switch to Beelzebub, much to everyone's shock. Yu tries to stop himself from attacking, while Kunino-sagiri says no one will get in his way. Nanako's voice gets through to Yu, who manages to stop himself, giving the others the chance to attack Beelzebub and Kunino-sagiri. Yu manages to destroy the antenna controlling him to catch Nanako after Kunino-sagiri drops her. However, Kunino-sagiri takes control of the others. Still in pain after grabbing the antenna, Yu hears Dojima's voice asking him to save Nanako, giving him the strength to fuse four Personas into the powerful Kohryu, using the Persona to free his friends, who all use their Personas to attack Kunino-sagiri, destroying him. However, the Shadows that created Kunino-sagiri threaten everyone until Nanako helps Yu summon Sraosha to purify the area of Shadows. Everyone returns to the real world to bring Nanako to the hospital, where she is placed in intensive care. Naoto feels bad that because she questioned Namatame, it took up time to save Nanako, but Yu says she did help out in the end. A couple of weeks later, Inaba is filled with a thick fog, and as Yu, Chie, Yukiko, and Yosuke are on the way to school, Yosuke tells the others that the police are interrogating Namatame, who has awakened. Yu also tells them that Nanako is feeling better, so they can all see her. Rise and Kanji also hear the good news, but Rise could not find Naoto. Yu finds her and tells her about the events, and she realizes that she actually did help out, even if she felt that she could only help out as a detective. The group goes to see Nanako after school, but she is still a little weak. Later, Adachi tells the group that they found info in Namatame's diary that he tried to hit on Saki Konishi which may have led to her death, which angers Yosuke, causing Adachi to leave to check up on Dojima. Yu tells Yosuke not to be upset and he should air his feelings, but he is not ready. As they head home, they pass by people talking about the fog which is very thick lately, reminding them of the fog in the TV world. Just then, Kanji puts on his glasses and urges the others to do so. When they do, they see that the glasses are allowing them to see through the fog, causing Chie to wonder aloud if the fog from the TV world is coming into the real world. A week later, they still cannot figure out why the TV world fog is leaking into their world, until Teddie mentions that now that they have discovered the real killer he has to go back, but he does not want to until Nanako is better. Yu tells him he can stay until then, making him happy. When Chie mentions how cold it has gotten, it reminds Yu that he promised to buy a new kotatsu for Nanako. They all plan to throw a party for Nanako for Christmas when suddenly Yu receives a call from Adachi that Nanako's condition has taken a turn for the worse. He heads to the hospital and sees Nanako just as she appears to die in front of him.

The team grieves after the apparent death of Nanako, while Dojima storms off to Namatame's room to confront him, but is stopped because of his injuries. After hearing a crash from Namatame's room, the group enters to find the man, seemingly attempting to escape through a window. Namatame's Shadow then appears on the Midnight Channel on the room's TV, boasting that it will never cease its desire to "save" people. Enraged, and faced with the possibility of Namatame being released through lack of solid evidence, the team considers what to do, with Naoto suggesting that he would likely meet his doom if thrown in the TV. Yosuke and Kanji agree with this, while Chie, Yukiko, and Rise attempt to change their minds. Yu begins to drag a helpless Namatame toward the TV and begins to push him in, but then changes his mind, much to Yosuke's anger. Yu proclaims he is not convinced that they have the full story, and he only wants to know the full truth; he tells Yosuke to calm down, and Naoto realizes that they never heard Namatame's side of the story yet. The team, mostly regaining their composure, agrees with Yu's wishes and leaves. They discuss their decision while trying to find Teddie, since he was by Nanako's side when they last saw him. Outside, everyone departs, leaving Yu alone for a moment as snow falls. Yu remembers his promise with Nanako to play in the snow, and begins to break down, though Yosuke returns to comfort him. The next day, the team realizes that the warning letters that Yu received are incongruent with Namatame's claims of "saving" people, pointing out the use of "don't rescue" and "will be put in and killed". Upon the team's request, Namatame relates his discovery of the Midnight Channel and his ability to enter the TV when he saw Mayumi Yamano on the Midnight Channel, and learning of her death. Unable to save the woman he loved, he attempted to warn the next victim, Saki Konishi, of the danger of her appearance on it, though he was again unsuccessful. When Yukiko appeared, he decided to take matters into his own hands by kidnapping and throwing her into a TV, since he believed it was the one place the murderer would not be able to reach. Since Yukiko did not die (due to Yu and his friends), he believed that he was successful, and repeated his method with the other members of the team, while he began to fancy himself a savior. Elsewhere, on an unknown, fog-covered street, Teddie is shown wandering, saddened that he was unable to protect Nanako, and says farewell to her and the team. In the hospital room where Nanako is being kept, Teddie's farewell to her is heard, and Nanako silently revives. In the next scene, Yu, Dojima, and the rest of the group is overjoyed to see that Nanako has miraculously revived, even though Teddie remains missing. Back home, a relieved Yu falls asleep, while his cellphone lights up on its own, revealing text messages from all of his friends. In the Velvet Room, Igor remarks on his long journey and how their guest has acquired many bonds along the way. Margaret reveals that the friendships their guest has gained has formed the Judgement Arcana. She then expresses her jealousy at the bonds he has made, before realizing a bond has formed between herself and the guest as the Empress Arcana. She remarks that their limousine will be parked for a while until they can figure out the next direction they will travel. The next day, at the Aiya diner, the team meets to figure out who the real culprit is. Naoto steps out to get some air, and Yu goes to join her, but not before finishing Aiya's Mega Beef Bowl for the first time, much to everyone's shock. After Yosuke joins them, the three each contemplate who the real killer could be with the knowledge they have, when Yu seems to have an epiphany as he stares up at the snowing sky.

Teddie is in the Velvet Room where he reveals that he has discovered he is only a Shadow, but one that has acquired human emotions. He asks Yu to say goodbye to Nanako for him when he goes to Heaven, but Yu speaks to him and tells him Nanako is alive and well. At the Aiya diner, Naoto realizes the culprit must be someone close to them and thinks to bring it up to the group, but Yu plans on going to the hospital. Yosuke accompanies him, but first tells Yu that he is upset that he is both proud and jealous of how Yu has made friends, despite being from the city like him and getting his Persona. He then says the only way he will feel better is if they become equals if they had a fight, to let out all of their pent up emotions. At the diner, Naoto has just revealed her suspect to the others, and Yukiko remembers seeing him at the inn while Mayumi Yamano was staying there, and Chie determines that he would have also spoken to Saki Konishi. At the hospital, Yu mentions that Mitsuo Kubo testified at trial that he blacked out in the police interrogation room right after turning himself in. Dojima told him that no one believed Kubo until one officer interrogated him. Suddenly, Adachi shows up in front of them, and Dojima shows up, as well, asking Adachi where Namatame has gone. He reveals Namatame was transported into holding, angering Dojima as he wanted to ask Namatame questions considering his alibi. Yu and Yosuke then confront Adachi about Yamano and Saki, to which he has no answer, and after he reveals he forgot to send the threat letter to the lab, Dojima gets angrier. Adachi tries to leave until Naoto confronts him, implying he is the one behind Yamano and Konishi's murders, and when confronted by Kanji, Adachi blurts out that Namatame threw all of them into the TV. With this slip, Naoto recalls that Adachi was not surprised that Morooka's death was not in Namatame's diary, as no one in the police had yet determined Kubo's murder of Morooka was a copycat killing. Adachi runs into Namatame's empty hospital room and disappears, while everyone realizes a TV is in the room. Elsewhere in the hospital, Teddie goes to see Nanako, who says she dreamt that he went away, but she could hear his voice. Nanako falls back asleep, and Teddie vows he will no longer run away. In the TV world, Rise is having difficulty finding Adachi anywhere, wishing that Teddie was there to help. Yu spots him nearby, and everyone says they missed him. He reveals what he has discovered about himself to the others, and they all tell him because he has a Persona, he is something more than a Shadow and more like them. Cheered up, Teddie suddenly picks up on Adachi's scent and brings the group to the first place they ever visited in the TV world, finding Adachi there. Yu asks him if he is truly the murderer, but he dismisses the accusation to reveal that the real world and TV world will soon be merging and that all humans will become Shadows. Rise realizes they are not speaking to the real Adachi, and then the Adachi walks off into a portal, leading everyone to Magatsu Inaba. Inside, Adachi claims that he is the king of the TV world before summoning the Reaper to attack them. Kanji and Naoto hold off the Reaper, letting the others follow an Adachi to the Amagi Inn where he reveals he threw Yamano into the TV world after she rejected his advances. Another Reaper appears, and Chie, Yukiko, and Rise hold it off, letting Yu, Yosuke, and Teddie follow Adachi's scent to a version of the police station, where Adachi shows that he threw Saki Konishi into the TV for also rejecting his advances while he was interrogating her. Another Reaper appears, and Teddie and Yosuke hold it off so Yu can confront the real Adachi who first complains that Mitsuo Kubo's copycat killing would have ruined his game. He wanted to make Inaba more exciting since he was passed up a job in the big city, but as Yu and the others went to save Kubo and Namatame began his "salvation" again, the game did not end. Adachi then proclaims that he would have had no problems so long as Yu and the others paid more attention to their studies, before proclaiming he wants none of them in the new world he will rule. He states they will have a final showdown to determine who the TV world prefers, summoning his own Persona Magatsu Izanagi, while Yu summons the real Izanagi.

He reveals Namatame was transported into holding, angering Dojima as he wanted to ask Namatame questions considering his alibi. Yu and Yosuke then confront Adachi about Yamano and Saki, to which he has no answer, and after he reveals he forgot to send the threat letter to the lab, Dojima gets angrier. Adachi tries to leave until Naoto confronts him, implying he is the one behind Yamano and Konishi's murders, and when confronted by Kanji, Adachi blurts out that Namatame threw all of them into the TV. With this slip, Naoto recalls that Adachi was not surprised that Morooka's death was not in Namatame's diary, as no one in the police had yet determined Kubo's murder of Morooka was a copycat killing. Yu asks him if he is truly the murderer, but he dismisses the accusation to reveal that the real world and TV world will soon be merging and that all humans will become Shadows. Rise realizes they are not speaking to the real Adachi, and then the Adachi walks off into a portal, leading everyone to Magatsu Inaba. Inside, Adachi claims that he is the king of the TV world before summoning the Reaper to attack them. Kanji and Naoto hold off the Reaper, letting the others follow an Adachi to the Amagi Inn where he reveals he threw Yamano into the TV world after she rejected his advances. Another Reaper appears, and Chie, Yukiko, and Rise hold it off, letting Yu, Yosuke, and Teddie follow Adachi's scent to a version of the police station, where Adachi shows that he threw Saki Konishi into the TV for also rejecting his advances while he was interrogating her. He wanted to make Inaba more exciting since he was passed up a job in the big city, but as Yu and the others went to save Kubo and Namatame began his "salvation" again, the game did not end. Adachi then proclaims that he would have had no problems so long as Yu and the others paid more attention to their studies, before proclaiming he wants none of them in the new world he will rule. He states they will have a final showdown to determine who the TV world prefers, summoning his own Persona Magatsu Izanagi, while Yu summons the real Izanagi.

He threatens to shoot Yu, as the others have problems dealing with the Reapers. Elsewhere, Rise uses Himiko to analyze the object, seeing it is a large collection of energy that is falling to the ground, while Chie and Yukiko realize his plan is insane. Adachi adds that once they become Shadows, they will not have to have emotions and will act only on instinct. This prompts Yosuke and Teddie to lash back at the Reaper, as it is revealed that the real Adachi had not shot Yu. However, as Magatsu Izanagi attacks the real Izanagi, Yu reacts in pain. Adachi calls him out on treating everything like a game to distract him from his boring life, and that he should not be seeking out the truth as Namatame is all the police needed to catch. However, Yu says that is not the truth he wants to seek, and that Adachi's excuses do not make up for what he did. Elsewhere, the groups of his friends take out the Reapers attacking them while also expressing their distaste in Adachi's plans. Adachi uses Magatsu Izanagi to make one last stand, but Yu and Izanagi take him out, destroying Magatsu Izanagi. Realizing he has lost and that there is no longer another world to go back to, Adachi decides to kill himself, but the dark force in the sky picks him up and uses him to say to the others that it will rule over the new world, revealing itself as the strange object hidden within Shadow Teddie months before. Yu asks who it is, and it reveals it is Ameno-sagiri, a being that controls the fog that covers both worlds and awoken by human desires as it attacks them. In the real world, Yu's friends see a strange object in the sky. In the TV world, Yu uses Isis to free himself from rubble as Himiko's analysis reveals Ameno-sagiri is what is bringing the two worlds together, as it reveals it is doing so because people can no longer differentiate between reality and fantasy, so fantasy will reign supreme. Everyone sends their Personas to try to keep Ameno-sagiri from crashing into the ground, while Ameno-sagiri reveals that their ability to face their Shadows to obtain Personas have only been a means for its plans to proceed, as the TV world only shows what people want to see. Naoto realizes that this is why they saw Namatame's Shadow not saying his inner thoughts, but what they wanted to hear him say. However, Ameno-sagiri wonders if their Personas are what are meant to be humanity's future, before proclaiming that it will test them to find out, pushing the Personas off of itself. It picks up Yu, wondering why he resists so much as he is alone, and the bonds he has with his friends are lasting. As he says his friends will always be with him and he will never give up, everyone in the group call out to him when they realize he is in danger and their Personas react. The Preacher delivers fire and brimstone sermons that consumption of meat is evil, because it leads to homosexual behavior. The new ban is hypocritical, as the Preacher himself continues to eat meat in private. Hurlan is attracted by the smell but the Preacher deflects attention from himself by insisting that Hurlan's soul is in danger if he continues to want meat. The Preacher takes him on a weekend prayer retreat in the woods to Camp Praythegayaway, but he soon becomes lost. Awakening, Hurlan is convinced that his desire to eat meat actually did result in some sort of homosexual-orgy-apocalypse, which destroyed human civilization. Hurlan therefore settles into the camp and attempts to rebuild civilization from scratch. Meanwhile, with Hurlan missing, Boss Hoss's video will instructs that Hambrosia will lead the town in his absence. Finally in charge, she decides to "cut loose" by listening to vinyl records and taking a bite of tobacco chaw - which nearly kills her. Hambrosia subsequently bans all forms of tobacco from town, and goes door to door with a shotgun in hand to make sure the ban is in effect. However, Hurshe one-ups her sister by making her own smoke-easy in the local bar. Hurshe makes up her own phoney religion of "Chawstafarianism" and claims the legal loophole that chaw is her religion's "sacred herb" and thus cannot be regulated. The two sisters find themselves at loggerheads.

Poet and prose writer, author of 'Odes' and texts on the work of Alberto Caeiro. Biographical note: (Oporto, 1887–1936). He graduated in medicine and is an unconditional admirer of the Greek civilisation above all others, and considers himself to be an expatriate from Greece. Being a royalist he chooses to emigrate to Brazil in 1919 (Portuguese monarchy had been overthrown in 1910). In his neoclassical odes he ponders on the briefness of life, the inevitability of death and the helplessness of the human condition. This “sad epicure” tries to find some contentment through the acceptance of fate and self-discipline lives by Horatio’s a motto: carpe diem (seize the day).

Poet and prose writer, a pupil of Alberto Caeiro. Biographical note: Álvaro de Campos. (Tavira, Algarve, 1890 - ?). He studies naval engineering in Scotland. He feels a foreigner wherever he is. Suffocated by a tedious and monotonous existence, failing to see the meaning of life, he looks for new sensations and travels to the Far East. When he comes back he is a renewed man. He embraces the futuristic movement and worships industrialisation and scientific and technological progress, with its hectic relentless rhythm and continuous change. There is an ecstasy of the senses, his relationship with machines and charcoal and steel is almost erotic. But in the background of this modern world lurk the shadows of the assembly line, the pollution, the emptiness of material things. The darkness of what is to come —eventually Campos tires. In his third phase, profoundly disenchanted with the present, he evokes the long-gone days of his perfectly happy childhood.

table-1010-777.caption: Australian outbreaks
data: Death of two horses and one person, Mark Preston.
20 horses died or were euthanised. Two people infected, with one death, Victory (Vic) Rail who was a nationally prominent trainer of racing horses.
Death of one horse. A veterinarian involved in autopsy of the horse was infected with Hendra virus, and suffered a mild illness.

Death of four horses. Queensland veterinary surgeon Alister Rodgers tested positive after treating the horses. On 1 September 2009 after two weeks in a coma, he became the fourth person to die from exposure to the virus.
Death of one horse. Unusually this horse had HeV antibodies present in its blood at the time of death. How this immune response should be interpreted is a matter of debate.
Death of one horse. The second horse on the property tested positive to Hendra and was euthanised on 12 July 2011.
Death of one horse. A horse was found dead after being unwell the day before. HeV infection was confirmed on 17 August 2011.
Death of two horses. The 2 horses were found dead in a field. Both tested positive to HeV. The exact date of death is not known however HeV infection was confirmed on 17 August 2011.

One horse euthanised after testing positive. A horse died one week previous on the property may have died of HeV. On 15 October 2011 another horse on the property was euthanised following a positive HeV antibody test.
A horse that died or was euthanised on 3 January 2012 returned a positive HeV test on 5 January 2012.
One horse died. A dog returned a positive test but was subsequently cleared.

One horse died. On 27 July it was announced that two other horses on the property, showing clinical signs of the disease, were euthanised. Two dogs are being assessed, and the property remains quarantined.
One horse was euthanised after returning a positive HeV test. 15 horses on the property are being tested and quarantined, along with horses on neighbouring properties.
One horse died. The property with 13 other horses is quarantined.
One symptomatic horse euthanised; the following day returning a positive HeV test. The property, with seven other horses, quarantined.
One horse died. Four horses and four people from the property being assessed.
Death of one horse, a second horse vaccinated, 5 cats and a dog being monitored.
Six year old gelding died, several other horses, dogs and cats being tested. A dog from this property tested positive for HeV and was euthanised around 19 July 2013
One horse died, no other horses on property.
Eighteen year old unvaccinated mare died, other animals on property under observation.
Thirteen year old unvaccinated quarterhorse died, other animals on property under observation.
